speechtext:
Mr. Speaker, I have the pleasure and honour this morning of presenting a petition signed by several citizens of my constituency of Brant calling for the enacting of legislation that would provide for:
(a)	a referendum of the people binding upon Parliament to accept or to reject constitutional amendments proposed by the government;
(b)	the acceptance or rejection of the proposed amendments to be determined by (1) a majority vote of the total votes cast in the whole of Canada together with, (2) a majority vote in the majority of the provinces with the territories being given the status of one province.
